Fake Certificate

Alice’s school attendance is represented by a binary string S of length N.

If S[i] = 1, Alice was present on day i.

If S[i] = 0, Alice was absent on day i.

Alice wants to improve her attendance record. She can perform at most one operation:

Choose a contiguous substring consisting only of 0s.

Convert all those 0s into 1s (as if she submitted a medical certificate).

A substring is a continuous segment of a string.
For example, "aca" is a substring of "abacaba", but "aaa" is not.

Your task is to determine the maximum number of days Alice can be marked present after performing at most one operation.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer T — the number of test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains an integer N — the length of the string.

The second line contains the binary string S.

Output Format

For each test case, print a single integer — the maximum number of days Alice can be marked present after at most one operation.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10^4

1 ≤ N ≤ 2 × 10^5

S is a binary string.

The sum of N over all test cases does not exceed 2 × 10^5.

Example
Input
4
3
111
3
000
6
010010
6
001001
Output
3
3
4
4
Explanation
Test Case 1

Alice was present every day. No operation is needed.
Answer: 3

Test Case 2

Alice was absent every day. She can convert the entire string.
Answer: 3

Test Case 3

Zero-only substrings are:

[1,1]

[3,4]

[6,6]

Choosing [3,4] results in 011110.
Answer: 4

Test Case 4

Choosing the optimal zero-only substring results in 4 present days.


SOLUTION::

import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;

class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		// your code goes here
		Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
		int t=s.nextInt();
		while(t-->0){
		    int n=s.nextInt();
		    s.nextLine();
		   String str=s.nextLine();
		   int m=-1,c0=0,c1=0;
		   for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		   char ch=str.charAt(i);
		   if(ch=='1'){
		       c1++;
		       c0=0;
		   }
		   else if(ch=='0'){
		       c0++;
		   }
		     m=Math.max(m,c0);
		   }
		   System.out.println(m+c1);
		}

	}
}
